comment: Carter-Williams (CHI) gathers the ball with his right foot on the floor and takes a legal two steps prior to the pass.
Carter-Williams (CHI) and Anderson (HOU) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
[Observable in enhanced video] Harden (HOU) moves his pivot foot.
Lopez (CHI) sets the screen on Ariza (HOU) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Harden (HOU) makes incidental contact that does not affect Zipser's (CHI) SQBR.
Carter-Williams (CHI) makes contact with Harden (HOU) that affects his FOM.
Harden (HOU) makes marginal contact with Carter-Williams (CHI) that does not dislodge him from legal guarding position.
[Detectable with stop watch] Wade (CHI) and Lopez (CHI) are in the paint for longer than three seconds.
Wade (CHI) makes inicdental contact with Ariza (HOU) that does not affect his ability to retrieve the loose ball.
Ariza (HOU) makes incidental contact with Wade (CHI) that does not affect his ability to retrieve the loose ball.
Correctly called 24 second violation.
Harden (HOU) does not enter the lane until the ball hits the rim.
Lopez (CHI) is inside the restricted area and fails to leave the floor prior to the contact with Harden (HOU).
Lopez (CHI) makes contact with Gordon (HOU) that affects his driving shot attempt.
Gordon (HOU) makes incidental contact with Wade (CHI) that does not affect his SQBR.
Gordon (HOU) makes contact with the ball.
Ariza (HOU) tips the ball with his hand and does not intentionally kick it.

Officials go to replay review for the out of bounds, but the call on the floor was a kicked ball violation. The call on the floor stands because kicked ball violations are not reviewable and the shot clock is reset to 14.
Gibson (CHI) moves his pivot foot before releasing his dribble.
Zipser (CHI) does not give Harden (HOU) room to land following the jump shot attempt.
Mirotic (CHI) makes marginal contact with Beverley (HOU) on the screen.
Lopez (CHI) sets the screen on Beverley (HOU) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Zipser (CHI) commits a take foul on Harden (HOU).
